    <h1>Recursion</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Nievergelt &amp; Hinrichs &middot; Ch. 2 &middot; <a href="https://textbookequity.org/algorithms-and-data-structures/">Algorithms and Data Structures</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A recursive algorithm solves a problem by solving smaller instances of the same problem. <strong>Divide and conquer</strong> splits the input, solves each part, and combines the results. The <strong>master theorem</strong> tells you the cost without unrolling the recurrence.</p>
    </div>

